			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> keynote:</span><br><i>Addressing Cognitive and Social Challenges in Designing and Using Ontologies in the Biomedical Domain</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MargaretAnneStorey.html">Margaret-Anne Storey</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_1">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_1</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s main topic is the design and use of ontologies, focusing on practical challenges in ontology work.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The core issues discussed are cognitive and human factors (understandability, collaboration) affecting ontology use.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6g.html"><span class="tagL">T6G: Socio-technical</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly frames ontology engineering as a socio-technical activity involving social processes and coordination.
</li></ul></li></ul>
